#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/design-and-build/vercel-react-best-practices/rules/rerender-use-deferred-value.md
M|rules|title: Use useDeferredValue for Expensive Derived Renders
M|rules|impact: MEDIUM
M|rules|impactDescription: keeps input responsive during heavy computation
M|rules|tags: rerender, useDeferredValue, optimization, concurrent
M|rules|When user input triggers expensive computations or renders, use `useDeferredValue` to keep the input responsive. The deferred value lags behind, allowing React to prioritize the input update and rende
M|rules|**Incorrect (input feels laggy while filtering):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|function Search({ items }: { items: Item[] }) {
M|rules|const [query, setQuery] = useState('')
M|rules|const filtered = items.filter(item => fuzzyMatch(item, query))
M|rules|return (
M|rules|<>
M|rules|<input value={query} onChange={e => setQuery(e.target.value)} />
M|rules|<ResultsList results={filtered} />
M|rules|</>
M|rules|)
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (input stays snappy, results render when ready):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|function Search({ items }: { items: Item[] }) {
M|rules|const [query, setQuery] = useState('')
M|rules|const deferredQuery = useDeferredValue(query)
M|rules|const filtered = useMemo(
M|rules|() => items.filter(item => fuzzyMatch(item, deferredQuery)),
M|rules|[items, deferredQuery]
M|rules|)
M|rules|const isStale = query !== deferredQuery
M|rules|return (
M|rules|<>
M|rules|<input value={query} onChange={e => setQuery(e.target.value)} />
M|rules|<div style={{ opacity: isStale ? 0.7 : 1 }}>
M|rules|<ResultsList results={filtered} />
M|rules|</div>
M|rules|</>
M|rules|)
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**When to use:**
M|rules|- Filtering/searching large lists
M|rules|- Expensive visualizations (charts, graphs) reacting to input
M|rules|- Any derived state that causes noticeable render delays
M|rules|**Note:** Wrap the expensive computation in `useMemo` with the deferred value as a dependency, otherwise it still runs on every render.
M|rules|Reference: [React useDeferredValue](https://react.dev/reference/react/useDeferredValue)